\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb480\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 INT. TRAIN PLATFORM}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Aaron and the Guard run onto the platform from the dark tunnel. There are no trains, no people, only an empty tile floor and a few concrete columns. Laser blasts and small explosions can be heard from the top of the stairs. A battle rages just beyond their view.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 What the hell is going on up there?}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 GUARD 2}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 This will be the hard part.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 This? Like getting to this point was a cake walk?}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 GUARD 2}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 At the top of the stairs, are people who are willing to give their lives to protect you. Some of them no doubt already have.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 That's not possible, I don't even know anyone here.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 GUARD 2}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Please pay attention, we have less than 3 minutes.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I'm listening.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 GUARD 2}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Just beyond where the sentries are shooting, there will be a series of automated carts moving cargo to the bay for transfer. Those cargo containers are heavy and impenetrable. They'll make good cover for you to make your way to safety. I will provide cover fire while you make your way past.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 You're not coming with me?}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 GUARD 2}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Your chances of boarding the ship are greatly increased if I can draw fire away from you. Ideally, you won't even be noticed. Are you ready?}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Board the ship? This is crazy! All I want to do is get away from this madness. I need to find Ivy and leave!}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 GUARD 2}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The time line where you board that ship is the only one where you see Ivy again. You must do this.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A random grenade starts bouncing down the stairs toward them. Guard 2 races over to it, picks it up and attempts to throw it down the tunnel. The grenade barely leaves his hand before it explodes. Aaron is thrown back against the wall. Smoke and shrapnel fill the air. Pieces of Guard 2's arm land on the stairs. His arm, part of his head, and a chunk of his upper torso are missing. He leans against the wall looking at Aaron. Somehow he is still able to talk.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 GUARD 2}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 You must go. (broken digitized audio sounds) I'll be right behind you.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 This is so fucked up.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Aaron starts up the stairs looking for the source of the grenade.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb480\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 INT. WORLD GATE CARGO DOCKS}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The docks are at the base of a massive cylindrical structure, built inside an impossibly huge hangar. Catwalks reach out from the walls of the silo in every direction. A moat-like ring of water surrounds the foot of it. And just past that, are armed men and women engaged in a frenzied fire-fight. Sentry turrets seem to have them pinned down for a moment, until a well tossed grenade destroys it in a brilliant ball of lightning. One of the machines Guard 2 described rounds the corner and rolls through the fray. Some of the laser fire bounces harmlessly off the large dark blue cases on the trailer behind it. He watches it's path and sees it pass unimpeded through a steel doorway past the fighting. Aaron makes his way along the edge of some large barrels, boxes and pipes trying to stay hidden. He watches for his opportunity to sneak past with one of the machines. Suddenly he's noticed by a woman in blue body armor.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Aaron?!? What the hell are you doing here?}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 I thought this was the way out?}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 You got turned around, its the other way.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She points down the hallway where Aaron came from. Suddenly a tank-like machine rolls around the corner just past where she's pointing. It fires a short burst of gunfire at her armor. She gets knocked back a step and then lurches forward tackling Aaron. }
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Shit! Hide in here!}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 She gives Aaron a small shove through a doorway marked "Quarantine Cargo Hold - WARNING: Ship to shore transfer room". She attempts to return fire on the machine but it launches a rocket at her. She dives into the room with Aaron as the rocket explodes farther down the docks.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb480\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 INT. QUARANTINE CARGO HOLD}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The small white room is mostly empty, except for 2 of the dark blue crates they saw on the cargo mover outside.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 What is that thing?}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 B-48: X class. I don't have what I need to take it down. }
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 What can I do?}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Lets see if there's anything useful in those crates.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Aaron watches the woman slide open a control panel on the nearest crate revealing a grid of glowing buttons. She presses one of them and begins opening her crate.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The crate near Aaron has a similar panel. Aaron kneels down and examines the buttons. He presses one marked "unseal". His crate slowly opens.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Inside the case he finds a series of gas canisters with bio-hazard symbols on them. }
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Damn, that's not good. What'd you get?}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Aaron shuts the case and presses the seal button.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Atomic printer. If we had more time and a power source, we could build whatever we wanted. How about yours?}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Just then, a grenade rolls up to the room, inches outside the open door.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2880\ri2160\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 (pointing)}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Grenade!}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The woman jumps to the door controller and smashes the button with her fist. Steel double doors with windows slam shut, less than a second before the grenade explodes.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Fuck, that was close!}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Through the windows, the tank like machine can be seen rolling up to the door.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 It's still coming!}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The machine slams into the door and makes a significant dent. The woman readies her weapon to fire at it as soon as it enters. It crashes into the door again, making the dent much worse. Sparks shower from the edges of the door controller. Before the machine can make another blow, a ball of lightning flashes in it's center for a moment - then it explodes. As the smoke clears, Guard 2 steps into view. He's a complete wreck, but still able to walk and use his remaining arm. }
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Hey, you made it!}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 No! Oh my god, no!}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 GUARD 2}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 (slightly garbled) Time to go.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Guard 2 puts his palm on the panel outside the door. A yellow light begins spinning in the center of the ceiling. A buzzing alarm starts ringing intermittently. }
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 No, no! You son of a bitch, you can't do this to me!}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Woman begins hopelessly hitting the button for the door, but it's too badly damaged to open. The buzzing alarm stops. }
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 What's going on?}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 We're being transferred to the ship's hold!}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Great! Isn't that good?}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The room begins to fill with a powerful white light.}
\par\pard\plain \li3600\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 WOMAN IN ARMOR}
\par\pard\plain \li2880\ri2160\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 (surprised)}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Who are you?}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The light reaches a blinding level, followed by the crackling water sounds Aaron heard only recently when he arrived.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 When the light passes, Aaron and the Woman are standing near the same crates as a moment before, but now the walls and lights are different.}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb480\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 INT.SHIPS QUARANTINE CARGO HOLD}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 This room is the same size, but the walls and floor are tan. A persistent red flashing light is mounted on the wall. The wall where the door was now has a working closed door and 2 large windows. A gray metal hallway lit with the same flashing red light can be seen through the inches thick glass. Aaron seems only mildly disoriented, but the woman collapses to the floor. Aaron rushes over to her and attempts to wake her.}
\par\pard\plain \li5040\fi-1440\ri-360\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 AARON}
\par\pard\plain \li2160\ri1440\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Hey, stay with me! I think we're going to be OK!}
\par\pard\plain \li720\ri-720\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\ql\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The Woman suddenly draws a deep breath and opens her eyes. She looks at Aaron confused and then around the room, before attempting to sit up.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Suddenly the entire room seems to tilt and everything is thrown to the far wall. The crates smash against each other with incredible force. The tan metal walls are dented from the impact. Aaron and the Woman are sent through the air like rag dolls, landing on top of the crates. }
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 They are unable to move before the room tilts again and everything is sent to the adjacent wall. Aaron and the Woman are thrown against the crates and the walls repeatedly as the room continues to make sudden wild shifts in momentum. }
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Through the thick glass windows the metal hallway suddenly explodes, sending chunks of metal out into a snowy landscape now visible through the resulting hole in the wall. Random small items are sucked out the gaping breach and fire roars at the edge of the window outside. }
\par\plain {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 An incredibly loud explosion shakes the room and for a moment Aaron, the Woman, and both heavy blue crates are seen floating weightless. The scene out the window shows mountains, then sky, then snow, then mountains, then a huge airship being destroyed in the air above them. The impact with the ground knocks Aaron out.}
\par\pard\plain \li6480\ri-173\sb240\sl-240\slmult0\qr\ltrch\loch {\f2\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 CUT TO BLACK }
